500|$|By the 21st century, ANAK {{comprised}} {{at least}} 1,100graduates, {{faculty members and}} honorary members. Among current Georgia Tech students, only upperclassmen (junior and senior undergraduates) are eligible for regular membership. Honorary memberships for faculty members and distinguished alumni are also available. The society apparently selects members based on [...] "leadership ability, personal achievement, strong character, and love for Georgia Tech". Membership is unrestricted by <b>race</b> <b>or</b> <b>gender,</b> and academic achievement is not considered in the selection criteria. The society admitted its first female member, Carol A. Burtz, in 1976, 23 years after Georgia Tech began admitting women.|$|E
